# Per-seed full per-step loss traces are large (~1.2 MB each at m=8); kept
# locally for inspection but not committed. The compact endpoint cells
# (seed_<NNN>.json) and the rolled-up seed_sweep.json ARE committed.
**/_runs/**/*_trace.json
# Dispatcher job logs + heartbeat are ephemeral run state.
**/_runs/**/*.log
_progress.json
# crossover claim-locks (ephemeral)
**/_runs/**/*.claim
# Scratch per-ordering re-eval partials. They are merged into the committed
# reference/seed_scatter_ratios.json (the multi-rate Figure 2b data source) and
# are fully regenerable from the trained_seed_*.json operators.
**/reference/_multiratio_*.json
# NB: trained operators (trained_seed_*.json, ~8.7 KB each) ARE committed —
# they're a durable resource for re-evaluation / MSE computation per seed.
# The repo-root .gitignore ignores `results/**/trained_*.json` (regenerable
# per-cell artifacts in the main experiments); this negation re-includes the
# seed-sweep operators so eval_seed_basis.py works from a fresh checkout.
!**/_runs/**/trained_seed_*.json
